18 “An Act relating to insurance; amending 36 O.S. 2021,
Sections 985, 987, and 989, which relate to the
19 Property and Casualty Competitive Loss Cost Rating
Act; removing certain prohibition on determining
20 certain rates to be competitive; allowing rate to be
determined excessive based on actuarial review;
21 requiring Insurance Commissioner to send certain
objection to insurer; removing certain filing
22 requirements; requiring certain insurer to file
certain information within certain time period;
23 providing certain requirements for certain filings to
become effective; requiring certain insurer to file
24 certain information if certain filing requires
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3781 Page 1

1 certain supervision; allowing certain insurer to
request certain hearing; requiring Commissioner to
2 publish notice of certain rate increase on Insurance
Department website; allowing certain rate to be
3 determined to be excessive; removing certain
provisions allowing Commissioner to disapprove
4 certain rate only in certain situations; allowing
Commissioner to disapprove certain rates with certain
5 notice and opportunity for hearing; allowing
Commissioner to issue certain order after certain
6 rate goes into effect; removing certain requirements
that certain order not affect certain contract or
7 policy; removing certain provision allowing
Commissioner to issue certain order in certain
