13 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 36 O.S. 2021, Section 989, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 989. Improper Rates; Disapproval; Hearing.
16 A. Basis for disapproval.
17 1. The Insurance Commissioner shall disapprove a rate in a
18 competitive market only if the Commissioner finds, pursuant to
19 subsection B of this section, that the rate is excessive,
20 inadequate, or unfairly discriminatory pursuant to Section 985 of
21 this title.
22 2. The Commissioner may disapprove a rate for use in a
23 noncompetitive market only if the Commissioner finds, pursuant to
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3781 Page 9

1 subs ection B of this section, that the rate is excessive, inadequate
2 or unfairly discriminatory under this subsection.
3 B. Procedures for disapproval.
4 1. Prior to the expiration of a waiting period or an extension
5 thereof, made pursuant to subsection B of Section 987 of this title,
6 the Commissioner may disapprove, by written order, rates filed
7 pursuant to subsection B of Section 987 of this title with notice
8 and opportunity for a hearing. The order shall specify in what
9 respects the filing fails to meet the requirements of this act the
10 Property and Casualty Competitive Loss Cost Rating Act. Any insurer
11 whose rates are disapproved pursuant to this section shall be given
12 a hearing upon written request made within thirty (30) days of
13 disapproval.
14 2. If, at any time after the rate goes into effect, the
15 Commissioner finds that a rate applicable to insurance sold in a
16 noncompetitive market does not comply with the standards set forth
17 in Section 985 of this title, the Commissioner may, after a hearing
18 held upon not less than twenty (20) days’ written notice, issue an
19 order pursuant to subsection C of this section, disapproving such
20 rate. The hearing notice shall be sent to every insurer and
21 advisory organization that adopted the rate and shall specify the
22 matters to be considered at the hearing. The disapproval order
23 shall not affect any contract or policy made or issued prior to the
24 effective date set forth in the order.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3781 Page 10

1 3. If, at any time, the Commissioner finds that a rate
2 applicable to insurance sold in a competitive market is inadequate
3 or unfairly discriminatory under paragraph 2 or 3 of subsection A of
4 Section 985 of this title, the Commissioner may issue an order
5 pursuant to subsection C of this section disapproving the rate. The
6 order shall not affect any contract or policy made or issued prior
7 to the effective date set forth in the order.
8 C. Order of disapproval.
9 If the Commissioner disapproves a rate pursuant to subsection B
10 of this section, the Commissioner shall issue an order within thirty
11 (30) days of the close of the hearing specifying in what respects
12 the rate fails to meet the requirements of this act the Property and
13 Casualty Competitive Loss Cost Rating Act. The order shall state an
14 effective date no sooner than thirty (30) business days after the
15 date of the order when the use of the rate shall be discontinued.
16 This order shall not affect any policy made before the effective
17 date of the order.
18 D. Appeal of orders and establishment of reserves.
19 If an order of disapproval is appealed pursuant to Section 990
20 of this title, the insurer may implement the disapproved rate upon
21 notification to the court, in which case any excess of the
22 disapproved rate over a rate previously in effect shall be placed in
23 a reserve established by the insurer. The court shall have control
24 over the disbursement of funds from such reserve. The funds shall
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3781 Page 11

1 be d istributed as determined by the court in its final order except
2 that de minimus minimis refunds to policyholders shall not be
3 required.
4 E. All determinations made by the Commissioner under this
5 section shall be on the basis of findings of fact and conclusions of
6 law.
7 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2027.”
